5\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tzk1705564326555.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tzk1705564326555.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tzk1705564326555.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pur1665702796277\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define an Application Shell\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">An application shell is required to run Windows and character-based\n      applications.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"pur1665702796277__context_w3745ab1b5b1_w3746ab1b5_w3747ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pur1665702796277__p_d12647e1_d12648e1_d12649e1\">\n             You can also define a shell for customized\n            application server.</p>\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"pur1665702796277__topic_d12650e1_d12651e1_d12652e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n\t\tapplication definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n                       </div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"pur1665702796277__topic_d12653e1_d12654e1_d12655e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pur1665702796277__p_d12656e1_d12657e1_d12658e1\">To define an application shell:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5963e1_d5964e1_d5965e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the U-Bar, click Browse, select <code class=\"ph codeph\">prj</code>, then choose the project you want to open.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5966e1_d5967e1_d5968e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the template for the type of application shell you want to create. Drag and drop onto the project object in the Structure.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5969e1_d5970e1_d5971e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"pur1665702796277__p_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1\">Right-click the new application shell and click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span> to open it in the Application Shell Editor. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Notice that the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Shell Type</span> property indicates the type of\n               application shell. The value of this property determines the other properties and\n               triggers, if any, that can be edited for the shell.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5972e1_d5973e1_d5974e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the properties applicable for your application shell.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5975e1_d5976e1_d5977e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Properties</span>, click the More icon () to open the Define Application Shell Properties dialog.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5978e1_d5979e1_d5980e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the properties of the application shell as required, then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5981e1_d5982e1_d5983e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the script editor, write ProcScript to define the application environment and actions required to initialize the application.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pur1665702796277__li_d5984e1_d5985e1_d5986e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> to compile the application shell.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffc1705481850320.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define an Application Server Shell</a><p>Create a an application server shell when you want to define customized behavior for a Uniface server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dig1705473594272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Windows Application Shell</a><p>Create a Windows shell for Uniface applications that run on any supported Windows platform.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/apf1705474154305.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Character Mode Application Shell</a><p>Create a shell for Uniface applications that run in character mode on any supported platform, such as Unix or Linux.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5831385\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5831385\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define an Application Shell Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define an Application Shell An application shell is required to run Windows and character-based applications. You can also define a shell for customized application server. You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . To define an application shell: In the U-Bar, click Browse, select prj , then choose the project you want to open. In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the template for the type of application shell you want to create. Drag and drop onto the project object in the Structure. Right-click the new application shell and click Open to open it in the Application Shell Editor. Notice that the Shell Type property indicates the type of application shell. The value of this property determines the other properties and triggers, if any, that can be edited for the shell. Set the properties applicable for your application shell. In More Properties , click the More icon () to open the Define Application Shell Properties dialog. Edit the properties of the application shell as required, then click OK . In the script editor, write ProcScript to define the application environment and actions required to initialize the application. Click Compile to compile the application shell. Related Links Define an Application Server Shell Create a an application server shell when you want to define customized behavior for a Uniface server. Define a Windows Application Shell Create a Windows shell for Uniface applications that run on any supported Windows platform. Define a Character Mode Application Shell Create a shell for Uniface applications that run in character mode on any supported platform, such as Unix or Linux. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}